<p><img alt="2012 Summer Staff" height="413" src="Images/badger-creek/2012 summer staff.png" title="2012 Summer Staff" width="624" /></p>
<p>Come be a part of the OLC Staff!&nbsp;BYU-Idaho Outdoor Learning Center is looking for&nbsp;staff members who can live on site to work with youth and campus groups,&nbsp;help with&nbsp;ranch work, facilitate ropes courses, and lead team building workshops. This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to help teach others and&nbsp;learn new skills, while living at the base of the majestic Teton mountain range. Since this job provides a unique&nbsp;opportunity to teach, and facilitate groups, it is a great experience, especially for people in the Teacher Education or Recreation Management majors.</p>
<p>Because of the student-centered mission of the Outdoor Learning Center, applications can only be accepted from BYU-Idaho students.</p>
<p><br />&nbsp;For questions regarding the application itself or the application process, please contact our office staff at 456-2531, or badgercreek@byui.edu&nbsp;(Please call Monday - Friday, 9 AM - 5 PM).</p>
<p><strong>Click <em><a href="Documents/badger-creek/Generic_Summer_Staff_Application[1].docx" title="Fall Staff Application">here</a> </em>to download a copy of the Staff Application Form.</strong></p>
